We provision the IDE with the different files that you would need or that you might find

00:32:36.959 --> 00:32:40.319
at your job if you were doing this type of task.

00:32:40.319 --> 00:32:44.239
And we have an R Markdown document that guides you through the task.

00:32:44.359 --> 00:32:45.959
This is the first milestone.

00:32:45.959 --> 00:32:51.719
It's kind of like a hello world in some ways, but we gave you some data, we want you to

00:32:51.719 --> 00:32:55.359
open up, we want you to look at it, we want you to recreate something.

00:32:55.359 --> 00:33:02.280
In this case, we give them an image of a plot and we say, there's a function that does this.

00:33:02.280 --> 00:33:03.439
It's the hist function.

00:33:03.439 --> 00:33:07.719
We did not tell you about it this week, but we did tell you how to read help pages and

00:33:07.719 --> 00:33:08.719
learn about functions.

00:33:08.719 --> 00:33:11.640
So can you learn about this function and make this plot?

00:33:11.640 --> 00:33:16.239
And then we give them an extension, which is, okay, let's push this a little further.

00:33:16.239 --> 00:33:19.920
Maybe you could change the color, maybe you could scour that help page and learn about

00:33:19.920 --> 00:33:23.800
your options and try to apply it.

00:33:23.800 --> 00:33:24.800
This is the first milestone.

00:33:24.800 --> 00:33:32.400
They get more and more advanced as you become more comfortable with R.

