01:00:27.239 --> 01:00:31.399
Okay, I said one more question before the top of the hour, but I think this is an important

01:00:31.399 --> 01:00:37.479
one to address, and I see Devin, you just answered in the chat too, but Ramil asked,

01:00:37.479 --> 01:00:43.159
are there elements of building data pipelines and best practices, foundations for clinical

01:00:43.159 --> 01:00:44.159
trials?

01:00:44.159 --> 01:00:46.560
Devin, do you want to answer that one?

01:00:46.560 --> 01:00:50.280
There's kind of like two elements to it, like to me, when I think of the conversations around

01:00:50.280 --> 01:00:55.520
data pipelines, we think of like the orchestration components of like, I have a variety of things,

01:00:55.520 --> 01:01:00.000
I have some raw data, it gets processed a bit, you have some derivative data that you're

01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:04.639
going to then tabulate and visualize and do some other modeling activities potentially

01:01:04.639 --> 01:01:11.760
against, you know, Academy won't necessarily cover like how to deploy that data pipeline

01:01:11.760 --> 01:01:15.439
with whatever orchestration system you might use, whether that be like RStudio Connect

01:01:15.439 --> 01:01:22.479
or Posit Connect or some other pipeline, but inside the pipeline, the analysis activities,

01:01:22.479 --> 01:01:26.800
the managing and munging of the data, the visualization, the tabulation, those are the

01:01:26.800 --> 01:01:31.360
core concepts that are covered with that, so you should be set up to be able to think

01:01:31.360 --> 01:01:36.840
from like, I have raw data, I have insight objectives on the other end, like, what are

01:01:36.840 --> 01:01:40.120
the pieces that need to stack together to do that?

01:01:40.120 --> 01:01:47.159
Those are well within Academy's blue house.

01:01:47.159 --> 01:01:48.159
